I have been going to Africa Kine since before they moved to the large building on 116, they were across the street on 116 and it was a ground floor restaurant. However the portions have gotten a tad smaller especially for the lunch ( Chebu Djen)  It was in a plastic container vs the huge silver one overflowing with vast amount of food.

I come for the poisson and ask for 1/2 salad and 1/2 plantains. My friends have ordered other dishes and we all agree that everything we have had is delicious. The onions alone have changed the minds of picky eaters.  I see a bunch of low ratings for service. I disagree. This is a casual dining restaurant. I like that my order is taken, served, and I can spend time chatting up my company without interruptions. I have been at different times; afternoon, evening, 1:30am... and have never felt rushed. Through the years I have always found the staff to be friendly.
